<theme id="thm206">
<titleabbrev>Lesson %d</titleabbrev>
<title>Compound time of 9/8. Dotted quarter note</title>
<tocimage>img206.png</tocimage>


<para>In this lesson the compound time of 9/8 is introduced, as well as two
new rhythmic patterns. The 9/8 time has three beats and each beat is occupied by
a 8th note. The measure is occupied by a dotted quarter note.</para>

<score width="600" height="100" border="0">
    <type>short</type>
    <music_border>0</music_border>
    <control_play></control_play>
    <control_measures></control_measures>
    <music>
        (Metrica 9 8)(n a4 b. l)(n a4 c g+)(n a4 c)(n a4 c g-) )
        (c (n a4 b. l)(n a4 n.)(Barra Final))
    </music>
</score>

<part><title>Exercises</title>

<para>
<link linkend="thm206_E1">Exercise 1</link> - Train your ear and practise the
introduced rhythmic patterns.</para>

<para>
<link linkend="thm206_E2">Exercise 2</link> - Read scores containing the rhythms
studied in this lesson.</para>

</part>

</theme>

